node.text:
This circuit breaker lockdown teaches me that... we dont always need a plan, at times we just need to breathe, trust, let go and see what happens! 😍👍🏻
.
2.5 months of lockdown at home, I felt it's a learning journey. It changed me a little and let me appreciate even simpler things in life. E.g. Staying at home with family, seeing your siblings and friends. ♥️👍🏻
.
While we always learn dont take things for granted, I'm treasuring the quality time, also yearning the time to spend with siblings and buddies. 🥰👍🏻
.
It's been a while... ♥️👍🏻
.
What have u gained in this circuit breaker lockdown? .
Anyway my facebook live is coming real soon! Funny is I only manage to do this when lockdown is over. Will u still support? Haha

It is not easy when life does not go according to plan. However, I cherished time with family and I build on skills and learned new knowledge (that is acquired). I expanded my knowledge. I improved my Korean and reached new milestones. Learning a language is not impossible. I look forward to learning Chinese and Japanese better. Learning (especially languages) is the new flex. I will always have your back. 📚📖 #peaceandgoodhealth #themoreyouknow #knowledgeispower
